claim.claim-text:
42. A method comprising:
utilizing a photolithography light source, producing a spectrum that generates an aerial image having multiple best focus points at a photolithography workpiece, the light source comprising:
a narrow band gas discharge laser comprising a line narrowing unit comprising a diffractive wavelength selection element and a center wavelength tuning mechanism, the output comprising laser output pulses;
utilizing a bandwidth monitor, monitoring the output pulses to determine the bandwidth of individual laser output pulses, occurring during a series of pulses illuminating a selected portion of the workpiece;
utilizing a bandwidth tuning mechanism, broadening the effective bandwidth of the series of pulses by changing the nominal center wavelength of pulses within the series of pulses to be larger and smaller than a selected nominal center wavelength.

51. An apparatus comprising:
a photolithography light source producing a spectrum that generates an aerial image having multiple best focus points at a photolithography workpiece comprising:
a narrow band gas discharge laser comprising a line narrowing unit comprising a diffractive wavelength selection element and a center wavelength tuning mechanism, the output comprising laser output pulses;
a bandwidth monitor monitoring the output pulses to determine the bandwidth of individual laser output pulses, occurring during a series of pulses illuminating a selected portion of the workpiece;
a bandwidth tuning mechanism broadening the effective bandwidth of the series of pulses by changing the nominal center wavelength of pulses within the series of pulses to be larger and smaller than a selected nominal center wavelength.
